parameters:
"Yes, the contract of servitude has been safely broken, so
there's no problem."

"Thank goodness. There was a lot of shaking coming from the
room Selphie-san was in, so I was worried."

"I know this isn't the time for it, but... I was being
teased to the point of almost climaxing."

"Ah, that's incredibly tough, isn't it? If I hadn't been
prevented from going mad, I would have lost my mind too."

(They're talking so casually, but isn't this actually a
terrifying conversation?)

"Anyway, let's put aside the talk of Selphie's masturbation
for now. The only one left is Tina."

"If that's the case, Gugukas just reported some information
about Maroges."

"Those two were connected in this incident as well, so it
was quickly figured out."

"It's better to be quick, but did you also find out the
location?"

"It's the monster breeding research facility that was
supposed to be closed. It seems Maroges and Tina are there."

"Artificially inducing the growth of monsters... That's
supposed to be banned, right?"
"So maybe the monsters Maroges requested are also..."
"It's likely that everything was planned from the start."
"Yeah, I'll blow Maroges and that facility to smithereens."

"I agree with blowing them away, but I have one question.
According to what we heard from Suelle and the others, Tina
has been brainwashed and her memories rewritten, right?"

"If that's the case, even if the brainwashing is undone,
wouldn't she be without her memories or dominated by false
ones?"

"That part is okay. It was the same with Rise; even though
they say her memories were made to be forgotten, it doesn't
mean they're gone."

"Making her forget means, essentially, she just can't recall
them."

"That was proven when we lifted Rise's brainwashing and her
memories returned."

"And as for rewriting, it's not actually rewriting but
rather making her forget things and planting new memories at
the same time."

"So, when the brainwashing wears off, the forgotten memories
can be recalled, and Tina herself will be able to understand
that the planted memories are fake."

"I see, so if we break the contract's effect and the
brainwashing, Tina can return to her state before the
brainwashing."
"Then we can take down Maroges without any problems."

"Even so, it's likely not Maroges but probably the
brainwashed Tina who will be waiting for us."
"Let's make sure we're fully prepared before we head out."

The destination \C[2]Biological Research Institute\C[0] has
been added to the map.

The playable character has been changed from Rise to
Selphie.

Items that Rise was equipped with that Selphie can equip
have been unequipped.
